<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#9f9f5f"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lamprey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I can't remember how many skill points you get per level, roughly?  I know you get 4 at level 5.  How many do you get later on, at level 10, 20, whatever?  For instance, at what level would you have am***ed 20 points?<P>Also, does it cost the same to make a skill untrained from unusable ingame, as it does to make the skill trained during character creation?  What I want to do is pick up Item Magic later on.  Does this mean I have to spend 8 to change it from unusable to untrained, then another 8 to change it from untrained to trained?<P>Any answers/comments would be very helpful.  Thanks.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fiend of 9 Worlds</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">no to get something to the trained section regardless if it is untrained or unusable will cost the same amount<BR>so to get Item Enchant from unusable to trained will indeed cost 8 and to answer this question if you were about to ask it you can not move a skill from trained to specialized<P>as for when will you come by 20 skill points... what is that lvl 67 guys? i dunno but it is up there teehehe<BR>once you get to lvl 10 i believe it is every 2 lvls you gain a skill point<P>Archfiend</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Carhan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skill credits:<BR>  1 per lvl up to 10<BR>  1 per 2 levels for lvls 10-20<BR>  1 per 3 levels for lvls 20-30<BR>  etc....</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Indiana</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually....the point system goes like this:<BR>1pt/lvl up to lvl 10 = 9pts at 10th<BR>1pt/2lvls after 10 up to 20 = 5pts<BR>1pt/3lvls after 20 up to 32 = 4pts<BR>1pt/5lvls after 32<P>so 20 skill points would be level 42<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Donknow</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">As, I understand it, unusable is just that unusable.  If you want to use that skill at anytime in the game, you had better train it before starting that character.  Nothing seems to be written in stone, so I could be in error.  Now, untrained on the otherhand can be trained.  There aren't many skills that will be unusable.  If you pick up the calculator at crossroads, it shows those skills with a garnet symbol.  If they are of any passing interest, train them.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SonyTheThief</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Unusable just means that you cannot benefit from that skill in any way unless you train it.  I think they did this because it would be unfair for people who didn't pick healing, or alchemy, or the schools of magic to get any of the abilities if they didn't spend the points to train them.  You can still get a skill that is Unusable after you make your character by simply training it with the points you accumulate from leveling.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mystron</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">   Actually you can make unusable skills usable for a short duration if you are an enchanter mage.  Each skill has a corresponding positive or negative spell booster.  Use it and you can gain mastery (for 3-5 minutes) over a particular skill.  Not very useful at low levels since it only boosts by 10points/level of the spell. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
